- Given the single explicit preference (enjoying CDs) and common CD-enthusiast priorities (mastering, dynamic range, replayability, sonic variety), Greatest Hits, Vol. 1 is the better match: it offers natural mastering and wide dynamics, acoustic timbral variety, and sequencing that encourages repeated listens. Abbey Road is superb for an immersive, single-session ritual, but it is the reason I rejected it here in favor of the compilation’s stronger alignment with repeatability, dynamic nuance, and varied acoustic interest.

